Delicious starter. To make the recipe hotter add a few of the seeds to the stuffing. Instead of frying can be brushed with olive oil and cooked on the grill!

Rating: 3
I made these as part of an appetizer buffet for my Christmas Eve guests. Obviously can be spicy and takes a bit of time to make so if you're in a hurry this is not the recipe for you. I doubled it so cleaning and stuffing 24 jalapenos took time. I had a few leftover so the next day I just heated them well in a nonstick skillet. Very good.

